crates/fidius-core/src/package.rs.doc_comment:
Load and parse a `package.toml` manifest from a package directory.

The type parameter `M` is the host's metadata schema. If the `[metadata]`
section doesn't deserialize into `M`, this returns `PackageError::ParseError`.

# Example

```ignore
#[derive(Deserialize)]
struct MySchema {
category: String,
min_host_version: String,
}

let manifest = load_manifest::<MySchema>(Path::new("./my-package/"))?;
println!("Package: {} v{}", manifest.package.name, manifest.package.version);
println!("Category: {}", manifest.metadata.category);
```

crates/fidius-macro/src/lib.rs.doc_comment:
Define a plugin interface from a trait.

Generates a `#[repr(C)]` vtable struct, interface hash constant,
capability bit constants, and a descriptor builder function.

# Example

```ignore
#[plugin_interface(version = 1, buffer = PluginAllocated)]
pub trait Greeter: Send + Sync {
fn greet(&self, name: String) -> String;

#[optional(since = 2)]
fn greet_fancy(&self, name: String) -> String;
}
```

Implement a plugin interface for a concrete type.

Generates extern "C" FFI shims, a static vtable, a plugin descriptor,
and a plugin registry.

# Example

```ignore
pub struct MyGreeter;

#[plugin_impl(Greeter)]
impl Greeter for MyGreeter {
fn greet(&self, name: String) -> String {
format!("Hello, {name}!")
}
}
```

crates/fidius-test/src/lib.rs.doc_comment:
Testing helpers for Fidius plugin authors and hosts.

This crate provides the infrastructure the Fidius codebase uses internally
for its own tests, now exposed so downstream users don't have to reinvent
the wheel. Add it under `[dev-dependencies]` and you get:

- [`dylib_fixture`] — build a plugin crate's cdylib via `cargo build`,
cached across tests in the same process. Optional signing via
[`DylibFixtureBuilder::signed_with`].
- [`signing::fixture_keypair`] — deterministic Ed25519 keypair for tests.
- [`signing::sign_dylib`] — produce a `.sig` file next to a dylib.

# Example

```ignore
use fidius_test::dylib_fixture;
use fidius_host::PluginHost;

#[test]
fn loads_plugin() {
let fixture = dylib_fixture("./path/to/my-plugin").build();
let host = PluginHost::builder()
.search_path(fixture.dir())
.build()
.unwrap();
let plugins = host.discover().unwrap();
assert!(!plugins.is_empty());
}
